library(ggplot2)
# Create age groups
heart_attack_age <- cut(heart_attack$age, breaks = c(29, 39, 49, 59, 69, Inf), labels = c("29-39", "40-49", "50-59", "60-69", "70+"))

ggplot(heart_attack, aes(x = heart_attack_age, fill = factor(`diagnosis result of heart attack`))) +
  geom_bar() +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("blue", "orange"), labels = c("No Disease", "Disease")) +
  labs(title = "Diagnosis Result of Heart Attack by Age Group",
       x = "Age Group",
       y = "Number of people",
       fill = "Diagnosis") +
  theme_classic() +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(size = 12, face = "bold", hjust = 0.5, margin = margin(b = 20))) +
  geom_text(stat='count', aes(label=..count..), position=position_stack(vjust=0.5), size=3, color='black')
## Warning: The dot-dot notation (`..count..`) was deprecated in ggplot2 3.4.0.
##  Please use `after_stat(count)` instead.
## This warning is displayed once every 8 hours.
## Call `lifecycle::last_lifecycle_warnings()` to see where this warning was
## generated.

heart_attack_diagnosed <- subset(heart_attack, heart_attack$`diagnosis result of heart attack`  == 1)

gender_counts <- table(heart_attack_diagnosed$sex)

gender_df <- data.frame(gender = names(gender_counts), count = as.numeric(gender_counts))

ggplot(gender_df, aes(x = "", y = count, fill = gender)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", width = 1) + geom_text(aes(label = count), position = position_stack(vjust = 0.5)) +
  coord_polar(theta = "y") +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("orange", "blue"), labels = c("Female", "Male")) +
  labs(title = "Gender Distribution of Heart Attack Patients",
       fill = "Gender") +
  theme_void()

  • Hypothesis Test Performance between Two Population Means of Resting Blood Pressure
heart_attack_disease <- subset(heart_attack, heart_attack$`diagnosis result of heart attack` == 1)
no_heart_attack_disease <- subset(heart_attack, heart_attack$`diagnosis result of heart attack` == 0)

# Perform two-sample t-test on resting blood pressure variable
t.test(heart_attack_disease$`resting blood pressure`, no_heart_attack_disease$`resting blood pressure`)
## 
##  Welch Two Sample t-test
## 
## data:  heart_attack_disease$`resting blood pressure` and no_heart_attack_disease$`resting blood pressure`
## t = -2.5083, df = 272.56, p-value = 0.01271
## alternative hypothesis: true difference in means is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  -9.094801 -1.096240
## sample estimates:
## mean of x mean of y 
##  129.3030  134.3986

  • Regression Analysis
  • Blood Pressure
thall_dummy <- ifelse(heart_attack$`Thalium stress test result` == 0, "normal",
                      ifelse(heart_attack$`Thalium stress test result` == 1, "mild",
                      ifelse(heart_attack$`Thalium stress test result` == 2, "moderate", "severe")))

model <- lm(heart_attack$`resting blood pressure` ~ thall_dummy, data=heart_attack)
summary(model)
